        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 29 at 2:34PM MDT by NWS Pueblo CO</headline>
        <description>At 234 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Granada, or 14 miles west of Coolidge, moving northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and brief penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Holly, Granada, Hartman, and Bristol.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
